1. VISION &amp; POSITIONING
1.1 What Is Octopussy?
Octopussy is a production-grade, open-source, agentic AI platform built entirely on Capability-Centric Architecture (CCA) 0.2 by Michael Stal. It enables individuals, teams, and organizations to deploy autonomous AI agents — individually or in coordinated multi-agent teams — across any platform: macOS, Windows, Linux, single-board computers (Raspberry Pi, Jetson Nano), Docker containers, and Kubernetes clusters.
Octopussy is the operating system for autonomous AI agents: it handles agent lifecycle, LLM routing, memory, RAG, security, sandboxing, token budgets, scheduling, multi-agent coordination, observability, and extensibility — so developers focus exclusively on agent goals and behaviors.
Installation is intentionally frictionless:
pip install octopussy
octopussy install
octopussy start
octopussy status

