6. ACTOR MODEL &amp; AGENT ARCHITECTURE
OctopussyAgent (ABC)
│
├── StatelessOneShot          — executes once, returns result, terminates
├── StatefulLoop              — executes repeatedly until stopped; maintains state
├── ScheduledTaskDaemon       — wakes on cron schedule; executes; sleeps
└── [UserDefinedAgent]        — any user-registered subclass of OctopussyAgent

Each agent instance has:

inQ (asyncio.PriorityQueue) — receives inbound OctopussyMessage instances, ordered by MessagePriority (CRITICAL=0 processed first, then HIGH=1, NORMAL=2, LOW=3)
outQ (asyncio.PriorityQueue) — holds outbound OctopussyMessage instances, ordered by MessagePriority (CRITICAL=0 dispatched first, then HIGH=1, NORMAL=2, LOW=3)
A dedicated _message_loop() asyncio task consuming from inQ
A dedicated _outbound_dispatch_loop() asyncio task consuming from outQ and forwarding to MessagingCapability
A dedicated _heartbeat_loop() asyncio task emitting heartbeats every 30 seconds
An AgentStateMachine enforcing valid state transitions
A LoopGuard enforcing the iteration ceiling

Agent State Machine:
CREATED → IDLE → PROCESSING → IDLE
                ↘ ERROR → STOPPING → STOPPED
IDLE → PAUSED → IDLE
IDLE → STOPPING → STOPPED


