Dead Letter Queue (DLQ) — Normative Specification:
The DLQ stores every message that could not be delivered to its recipient after 3 consecutive delivery attempts. No message is ever silently discarded. Every DLQ entry contains: the full original OctopussyMessage, the failure reason, the attempt count, and the timestamp of the last failure. DLQ entries are persisted in SQLite (dlq_store.py) and survive system restarts.

