D-08 — ACTOR MODEL &amp; AGENT INTERNAL ARCHITECTURE

Spec ref: §6 — Actor Model &amp; Agent Architecture
Purpose: Shows the complete internal structure of every OctopussyAgent instance, its three asyncio tasks, injected ports, and subtype hierarchy.

OctopussyAgent (ABC)  [octopussy/capabilities/actor/essence/agent_base.py]
│
├── SUBTYPE HIERARCHY
│   ├── StatelessOneShot      — executes once, returns result, terminates
│   ├── StatefulLoop          — executes repeatedly until stopped; maintains state
│   ├── ScheduledTaskDaemon   — wakes on cron schedule; executes; sleeps
│   └── [UserDefinedAgent]    — any user subclass registered via UserAgentExtensionCapability
│
└── INTERNAL STRUCTURE (per agent instance)
    │
    ├── QUEUES
    │   ├── inQ   asyncio.PriorityQueue  ◄── receives OctopussyMessage (CRITICAL=0 first)
    │   └── outQ  asyncio.PriorityQueue  ──► dispatches OctopussyMessage (CRITICAL=0 first)
    │
    ├── ASYNCIO TASKS (three dedicated tasks per agent)
    │   ├── _message_loop()          ◄── consumes from inQ; Chain of Responsibility
    │   ├── _outbound_dispatch_loop()◄── consumes from outQ; forwards to MessagingCapability
    │   └── _heartbeat_loop()        ◄── emits heartbeat EVENT every 30 seconds
    │
    ├── COMPONENTS
    │   ├── AgentStateMachine        — enforces valid state transitions
    │   ├── LoopGuard                — enforces max_iterations ceiling
    │   │                              raises LoopLimitExceededError when exceeded
    │   ├── ConversationMemory       — in-memory conversation history for current session
    │   ├── ReflectionEngine         — implements ReAct / Reflection agentic patterns
