D-14 — PLUGIN ARCHITECTURE &amp; PLUGIN LIFECYCLE

Spec ref: §15 — Plugin Architecture
Purpose: Shows all 10 plugin types, the plugin manifest format, and the complete plugin lifecycle from load to hot-reload to unload.

  PLUGIN TYPES (PluginType enum — 10 types):
  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │  Type                    Purpose                                        │
  │  ──────────────────────  ──────────────────────────────────────────────│
  │  TOOL_PLUGIN             Add new tools to ToolRegistryCapability        │
  │  LLM_ADAPTER_PLUGIN      Add new LLM provider adapters                 │
  │  VLM_ADAPTER_PLUGIN      Add new VLM provider adapters                 │
  │  COMM_ADAPTER_PLUGIN     Add new communication channel adapters        │
  │  VECTOR_DB_PLUGIN        Add new vector database backends               │
  │  GRAPH_DB_PLUGIN         Add new graph database backends                │
  │  MCP_SERVER_PLUGIN       Register new MCP server endpoints             │
  │  INFERENCE_ENGINE_PLUGIN Add new local inference engine backends        │
  │  PROMPT_PATTERN_PLUGIN   Add new prompt patterns to PromptEngine        │
  │  USER_AGENT_PLUGIN       Register user-defined OctopussyAgent subclasses│
  │                          (NEW in v5.0)                                  │
  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  PLUGIN MANIFEST (plugin.json — required in every plugin directory):
  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │  {                                                                      │
  │    "plugin_id":              "my_plugin",                               │
  │    "plugin_type":            "USER_AGENT_PLUGIN",                       │
  │    "version":                "1.0.0",                                   │
  │    "entry_module":           "my_package.my_module",                    │
  │    "agent_type":             "my_custom_agent",  (USER_AGENT_PLUGIN)    │
  │    "agent_class":            "MyCustomAgent",    (USER_AGENT_PLUGIN)    │
  │    "description":            "A user-defined agent.",                   │
  │    "schema_version":         "5.0",                                     │
  │    "min_octopussy_version":  "5.0"                                      │
  │  }                                                                      │
  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  PLUGIN LIFECYCLE:
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  LOAD:  PluginCapability.load_plugin(plugin_dir)
         │
         ├── 1. Read and validate plugin.json schema
         │        FAIL → PluginValidationError (plugin not loaded)
         │
         ├── 2. Import entry_module (dynamic Python import)
         │        FAIL → PluginImportError
         │
         ├── 3. Type-specific registration:
         │        │
         │        ├── USER_AGENT_PLUGIN:
         │        │   └── UserAgentExtensionCapability
         │        │       .register_agent_class(agent_type, agent_class)
         │        │
         │        ├── TOOL_PLUGIN:
         │        │   └── ToolRegistryCapability.register_tool(descriptor)
         │        │
         │        ├── LLM_ADAPTER_PLUGIN:
         │        │   └── LLMRouterCapability.register_provider(adapter)
         │        │
         │        └── [other types: analogous registration]
         │
         └── 4. Register in PluginRegistry (plugin_registry.py)
                  → plugin is now active

  HOT-RELOAD:  PluginCapability.hot_reload_plugin(plugin_id)
         │
         ├── 1. Unload current version (gracefully)
         ├── 2. Re-import updated module
         ├── 3. Re-register with updated implementation
         └── 4. Zero system restart required

  UNLOAD:  PluginCapability.unload_plugin(plugin_id)
         │
         ├── 1. Deregister from type-specific registry
         ├── 2. Remove from PluginRegistry
         └── 3. Clean up imported module references

  PluginCapability NUCLEUS:
  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │  Essence:                                                               │
  │    PluginRegistry      — catalogue of loaded plugins                   │
  │    HotReloadManager    — manages live plugin replacement                │
  │                                                                         │
  │  Realization:                                                           │
  │    PythonModuleLoader  — dynamic Python module import                  │
  │    PluginStateStore    — persists plugin metadata (SQLite)              │
  │                                                                         │
  │  Adaptation:                                                            │
  │    PluginAdapter       — implements PluginContract                      │
  │    OctopussyMCPServer  — MCP 2025-11-25 server for built-in tools      │
  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘


