D-18 — TOOL EXECUTION WORKFLOW

Spec ref: §5 — Built-in Tools Catalogue; §11 — MCP Integration
Purpose: Complete workflow for a tool call from agent decision to sandboxed execution and result return.

  TRIGGER: Agent's process_task() decides to call a tool
                              │
                              ▼
  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │  STEP 1: PERMISSION CHECK                                               │
  │                                                                         │
  │  ToolRegistryCapability.PermissionChecker                               │
  │  • Checks tool_id against PermissionsSpec.allowed_tools                 │
  │  • Checks tool_id against PermissionsSpec.forbidden_tools               │
  │  • Absence of permission = DENIAL                                       │
  │                                                                         │
  │  FAIL → PermissionDeniedError (tool call aborted)                      │
  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                              │ PASS
                              ▼
  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │  STEP 2: INPUT VALIDATION                                               │
  │                                                                         │
  │  ToolRegistryCapability.ToolResultValidator                             │
  │  • Validates tool call input against tool's JSON schema                 │
  │                                                                         │
  │  FAIL → ToolInputValidationError                                        │
  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                              │ PASS
                              ▼
  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │  STEP 3: MCP ROUTING                                                    │
  │                                                                         │
  │  MCPClientAdapter                                                       │
  │  • Adds header: MCP-Protocol-Version: 2025-11-25                       │
  │  • Sends HTTP POST to OctopussyMCPServer (built-in tools)              │
  │    OR to External MCP Server (per MCPServerSpec)                        │
  │  • Streams response via SSE                                             │
  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                              │
                              ▼
  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │  STEP 4: SANDBOX PROVISIONING (if tool requires sandbox)               │
  │                                                                         │
  │  SandboxCapability.provision(agent_id, spec)                           │
  │  • Creates isolated execution environment per agent                    │
  │  • Applies resource limits:                                            │
  │    CPU: 1.0 cores | Memory: 512 MB | Disk: 1024 MB | Network: disabled │
  │  • Backend: Docker | gVisor | seccomp | macOS sandbox                  │
  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                              │
                              ▼
  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │  STEP 5: SANDBOXED EXECUTION                                            │
  │                                                                         │
  │  SandboxCapability.execute(agent_id, command, timeout_sec=30)          │
  │  • Tool runs in isolated subprocess / container                        │
  │  • Timeout enforced (default: 30 seconds)                              │
  │  • Network access: disabled by default (explicit allowlist required)   │
  │  • A misbehaving tool in Agent A CANNOT affect Agent B or host system  │
  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                              │
                              ▼
  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │  STEP 6: OUTPUT VALIDATION                                              │
  │                                                                         │
  │  ToolRegistryCapability.ToolResultValidator                             │
  │  • Validates tool output against tool's output JSON schema              │
  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                              │
                              ▼
  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │  STEP 7: SANDBOX CLEANUP (optional, per tool)                          │
  │                                                                         │
  │  SandboxCapability.destroy(agent_id)                                   │
  │  • Tears down sandbox if per-call isolation is configured              │
  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
                              │
                              ▼
  Tool result returned to process_task() for incorporation into LLM context

